title: Leaked specs and images of Gionee A1 reveal 5.5-inch 1080p display and 16MP selfie camera
text:
Leaked specs and images of Gionee A1 reveal 5.5-inch 1080p display and... Leaked specs and images of Gionee A1 reveal 5.5-inch 1080p display and 16MP selfie camera By - February 13, 2017 “The Gionee A1 will feature 4GB of RAM, 64GB of storage, Nougat and a 4,010mAh fast charging battery” 
Last week, Gionee sent out invites for its MWC press event scheduled for February 27th. The brand will be introducing the Gionee A1 and A1 Plus smartphones at the event. Now just a few days ahead of the unveiling, some alleged live images of the Gionee A1 have hit the interwebs. In addition, the specs and price of the phone have also been tipped. 
As seen in the live images, the Gionee A1 will flaunt an all-metal unibody design. The phone will be available in white and gold. It’s expected to come with a fingerprint sensor, which will be located at its rear below the main camera. The other expected specs include a 5.5-inch full HD display with 2.5D Gorilla glass, 1.8GHz octa-core MediaTek processor, and 4GB of RAM. 
The Gionee A1 will reportedly feature 64GB of expandable storage. The camera department will include a 16-megapixel selfie shooter and a 13-megapixel primary snapper. The phone will come with an IR blaster, dual-SIM slots, Android 7.0 Nougat with Amigo OS 4.0 and a 4,010mAh battery with 18W fast charging support. 
The source claims that the Gionee A1 will be launched in Nepal on March 15th, and will be priced there at around Rs 22,500. We will be on the floor at MWC in Barcelona later this month to get you all the official details, so stay tuned.
